# Power BI Advanced User Guide

## Advanced Data Modeling
- Creating complex data models with relationships
- Using DAX for calculated columns and measures
- Implementing time intelligence functions

## Advanced Visualizations
- Customizing visuals with advanced formatting options
- Using custom visuals from the Power BI marketplace
- Creating interactive dashboards with drill-through and tooltips

## Power BI Service Features
- Managing workspaces and content packs
- Configuring data refresh schedules
- Implementing row-level security for data protection

## Integration and Automation
- Embedding Power BI reports in other applications (e.g., SharePoint, Teams)
- Using Power BI APIs for automation
- Integrating Power BI with Microsoft Power Platform (Power Apps, Power Automate)

## AI and Machine Learning
- Leveraging AI features like Q&A and insights
- Integrating with Azure Machine Learning for predictive analytics

## Best Practices and Optimization
- Best practices for data modeling and report design
- Tips for optimizing performance and load times
- Data governance and compliance considerations

## Additional Resources
- [Advanced Power BI courses](https://www.coursera.org/learn/advanced-microsoft-power-bi) 
- [Advanced Power BI certifications](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/data-analyst-associate/?practice-assessment-type=certification)
